   <body xml:id="thebody" style="defaultCaption">
      <div xml:lang="en">
         <p begin="00:00:08.33" end="00:00:10.33" region="speaker">Once you have received your Digital Certificate,</p>
         <p begin="00:00:10.33" end="00:00:13.33" region="speaker">you will need to install it on your web browser.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:13.33" end="00:00:15.46" region="speaker">This video covers installation instructions</p>
         <p begin="00:00:15.46" end="00:00:17.00" region="speaker">for Firefox.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:17.00" end="00:00:20.23" region="speaker">In your browser&apos;s &quot;Menu bar&quot; click &quot;Tools&quot; and</p>
         <p begin="00:00:20.23" end="00:00:21.96" region="speaker">then &quot;Options.&quot;</p>
         <p begin="00:00:21.96" end="00:00:24.50" region="speaker">Open the &quot;Advanced&quot; tab.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:24.50" end="00:00:26.16" region="speaker">Then click the &quot;Encryption&quot; tab.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:26.16" end="00:00:30.63" region="speaker">Click the &quot;View Certificates&quot; button.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:30.63" end="00:00:32.43" region="speaker">Make sure the &quot;Your Certificates&quot; tab is</p>
         <p begin="00:00:32.43" end="00:00:36.70" region="speaker">selected Click the &quot;Import&quot; button.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:36.70" end="00:00:39.03" region="speaker">This will launch a browser window where you can then</p>
         <p begin="00:00:39.03" end="00:00:41.66" region="speaker">search for the saved Digital Certificate.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:41.66" end="00:00:43.56" region="speaker">Browse to the location where your Digital</p>
         <p begin="00:00:43.56" end="00:00:46.86" region="speaker">Certificate was previously saved Now select your</p>
         <p begin="00:00:46.86" end="00:00:48.86" region="speaker">digital certificate.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:50.16" end="00:00:53.00" region="speaker">Enter your private key&apos;s password.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:53.00" end="00:00:55.33" region="speaker">It is important to note at this point that neither</p>
         <p begin="00:00:55.33" end="00:00:59.03" region="speaker">the cert provider nor GSA can recover your password.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:59.03" end="00:00:61.96" region="speaker">Thus if you forget or lose it, you&apos;ll have to buy a</p>
         <p begin="00:00:61.96" end="00:00:63.43" region="speaker">new certificate altogether.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:63.43" end="00:00:68.86" region="speaker">Click OK A message will appear, informing you of a</p>
         <p begin="00:00:68.86" end="00:00:71.96" region="speaker">successful import of the certificate.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:71.96" end="00:00:74.03" region="speaker">You will see your digital cert show up under the</p>
         <p begin="00:00:74.03" end="00:00:76.03" region="speaker">&quot;Your Certificates&quot; tab.</p>
    </div>
